 hope the new one looks cleaner.<br /><br />It was done because the 2.1.x setup was meant to fix the problem without<br />needing to ever have two buffers. Essentially, the default buffer size of<br />2.1 should be the "native" 2k of isofs, so a directory entry should never<br />span two buffers any more (it used to be that Linux used a buffer size of<br />1kB and thus a "isofs buffer" of 2kB was spit into two "linux buffers"). <br /><br />Hmm.. Is the code broken someway (using 1kB buffers still?) or do you have<br />CD's that have directory names spanning across the "native" buffers too? <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
